body_html:
@bayandin After step 4 build and test, Go functions corresponding to TensorFlow operations are already generated in op/wrappers.go. This is why

go test github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tensorflow/go

passes. You are good to go.

If you want to regenerate Go functions, then use:

go generate github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tensorflow/go/op

Make sure TensorFlow repository is under GOPATH and you have Protocol buffer compiler 3.x

body:
@bayandin After step 4 build and test, Go functions corresponding to TensorFlow operations are already generated in op/wrappers.go. This is why 

`go test github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tensorflow/go`

passes. You are good to go.

If you want to regenerate Go functions, then use:

`go generate github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/tensorflow/go/op`

Make sure TensorFlow repository is under GOPATH and you have Protocol buffer compiler 3.x
